cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.SD 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on learning user representations from social media behavior. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also likely as the paper discusses using user representations to improve topic modeling and tweet-level stance classification. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses various machine learning techniques to learn user representations and evaluate their effectiveness. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of user representations in public policy research. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the integration of user features into existing classifiers.
